WEBVTT

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:04.940
There's always the custom that when a person is about

00:00:04.940 --> 00:00:07.360
to die, they first make a wish and then

00:00:07.360 --> 00:00:08.360
they bury them.

00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:13.760
There was a person who used a wheelchair

00:00:13.760 --> 00:00:15.800
and when he was about to die, with all his

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:17.740
family around his bed, he made his

00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:18.140
wish.

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:20.320
When I die, I want them to put it inside the

00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:21.320
coffin.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:25.720
And the family granted his wish.

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:27.680
The day of the funeral arrived, and the family

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.466
buried him with his wheelchair.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:33.640
The second person was blind, and when he was about to

00:00:33.640 --> 00:00:35.720
die, with all his family around his

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:37.100
bed, he made his wish.

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:39.620
I want that when I die, please, and the family

00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:40.420
granted it.

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:43.040
When he died, at the funeral they buried the blind

00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:46.326
person and placed his cane inside the coffin.

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:50.500
And the third was an oral deaf person, and when

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:52.340
he was about to die with all his family

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:53.700
he made his wish.

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:55.600
I wish, and his family granted it.

00:00:55.520 --> 00:00:57.840
When they buried him, they put the cochlear implant and

00:00:57.840 --> 00:00:59.983
the hearing aid inside the coffin.

00:01:01.340 --> 00:01:03.720
Then came a signing deaf person, and when he was about

00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:05.700
to die, he made his wish, and they

00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:06.620
granted it.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:10.640
When the burial was held, they brought the live interpreter

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:13.120
in handcuffs and buried her with the deaf person.
